class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> constructRectangle(int area) {
        for (int i = sqrt(area); i >= 1; i--) {
            if (area % i == 0) {
                return {area / i, i};
            }
        }
        return {};
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(area))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates from the square root of the area down to 1, checking for divisors. The first divisor found results in the desired length and width, minimizing the difference.

